<subSubSection id="00976504FFEB6871FF68C80263F7FCCC" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4832368FFFEB6871FF68C80263F7FCCC" blockId="27.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis id="7AF9EA9DFFEB6871FF68C8026305FD71" bold="true" box="[199,308,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="8F8D4D0CFFEB6871FEEDC80263AFFD70" box="[322,414,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deitzi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7AF9EA9DFFEB6871FEEDC80263AFFD70" box="[322,414,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">A. deitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="61CA57E6FFEB6871FE0AC80263CFFD71" box="[421,510,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" rank="species">
<emphasis id="7AF9EA9DFFEB6871FE0AC80263CFFD71" bold="true" box="[421,510,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
generally resembles 
<taxonomicName id="8F8D4D0CFFEB6871FD43C80261BEFD70" box="[748,911,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7AF9EA9DFFEB6871FD43C80261BEFD70" box="[748,911,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">A. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="61CA57E6FFEB6871FC39C80261C1FD71" box="[918,1008,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" rank="species">
<emphasis id="7AF9EA9DFFEB6871FC39C80261C1FD71" bold="true" box="[918,1008,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but is much more robust. The female 
<typeStatus id="9736882DFFEB6871FF38C8FE62C6FD5C" box="[151,247,656,680]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="8F8D4D0CFFEB6871FE8FC8FE634FFD5C" box="[288,382,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deitzi">
<emphasis id="7AF9EA9DFFEB6871FE8FC8FE634FFD5C" box="[288,382,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">A. deitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—the largest specimen in the genus (~ 
<quantity id="8F759B6AFFEB6871FC9AC8E16141FD5C" box="[821,880,655,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" unit="mm" value="8.0">8mm</quantity>
)—is identical to the 
<typeStatus id="9736882DFFEB6871FBC9C8E166F9FD5C" box="[1126,1224,655,680]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">holotype</typeStatus>
except for a more elevated and tectiform posterior process; its much lighter coloration could be an artifact from collecting or preservation. The species differs from other 
<taxonomicName id="8F8D4D0CFFEB6871FD0AC8B66124FD04" box="[677,789,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="7AF9EA9DFFEB6871FD0AC8B66124FD04" box="[677,789,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">Allodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a combination of features, including the variegated coloration pattern and the shape of the lateral plate in males, produced into a large finger-like process which is distinctly truncate apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="00976504FFEB6871FF68C92A6141FC51" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4832368FFFEB6871FF68C92A6141FC51" blockId="27.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis id="7AF9EA9DFFEB6871FF68C92A637FFCA9" bold="true" box="[199,334,836,861]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">Etymology.</emphasis>
The male 
<typeStatus id="9736882DFFEB6871FE65C92B601CFCA9" box="[458,557,837,861]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">paratype</typeStatus>
, previously studied by Deitz, was included in his classification of the higher categories of 
<taxonomicName id="8F8D4D0CFFEB6871FE93C90960E0FC74" authority="Deitz, 1975a: 150" authorityName="Deitz" authorityPageNumber="150" authorityYear="1975" box="[316,721,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Membracidae (
<bibRefCitation id="2C1C4B7EFFEB6871FE43C90960F9FC74" author="Deitz" box="[492,712,871,896]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" refString="Deitz, L. L. (1975 a) Classification of the higher categories of the New World treehoppers (Homoptera: Membracidae). North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station Technical Bulletin, 225 (i - ii), 1 - 177." type="journal article" year="1975" yearSuffix="a">
Deitz, 
<number id="FE4524A8FFEB6871FD90C909604BFC74" box="[575,634,871,896]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" value="1975.0">1975</number>
a: 
<number id="FE4524A8FFEB6871FD35C90960F9FC74" box="[666,712,871,896]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" value="150.0">150</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Owing to the relevance of his contributions to treehopper systematics, this newly discovered species is named in his honor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
